OL,3,C'Sleep disorder has taken over my
OL,4,Clife': Charity warns of a sleep
OL,5,Cpandemic
OL,7,FShe said: "I've not been able to work.
OL,8,FMy relationship with my husband is
OL,9,Fstrained because we've got to sleep in
OL,10,Fseparate beds. I've got no energy to
OL,11,Fplay with the kids like I used to.
OL,13,F"People have stopped inviting me out
OL,14,Fbecause I always say no because I'm
OL,15,Fjust so knackered. Every possible area
OL,16,Fof my life... the impact has just been
OL,17,Fhuge."
