OL,3,C'Sleep disorder has taken over my
OL,4,Clife': Charity warns of a sleep
OL,5,Cpandemic
OL,7,FMichelle, 44, began to struggle with
OL,8,Fher sleep in 2021 when she experienced
OL,9,Fhypnic jerks, involuntary muscle
OL,10,Fcontractions which are likened to the
OL,11,Fsensation of falling.
OL,13,FTriggered by a in her life, the
OL,14,Fjerking sensations would stop her from
OL,15,Fsleeping altogether.
OL,17,F"As soon as I was about to nod off to
OL,18,Fsleep, I would jump. This happened
OL,19,Fhundreds of times a night, stopping me
OL,20,Ffrom sleeping altogether", she said.
