OL,3,C'Sleep disorder has taken over my
OL,4,Clife': Charity warns of a sleep
OL,5,Cpandemic
OL,7,FIn a telephone consultation with a GP,
OL,8,Fshe was initially only offered an
OL,9,Fantihistamine, despite expressing how
OL,10,Fher lack of sleep made her life feel
OL,11,Fworthless.
OL,13,FAfter exhausting all options, Michelle
OL,14,Fthen turned to 's Sleep Laboratory,
OL,15,Fwhere she spent the night in order for
OL,16,Fher sleeping patterns to be examined.
OL,18,FMichelle described the experience as
OL,19,F"uncomfortable".
