OL,3,C'Sleep disorder has taken over my
OL,4,Clife': Charity warns of a sleep
OL,5,Cpandemic
OL,7,FThey said: "Like all NHS services, the
OL,8,FSleep Centre has seen a significant
OL,9,Frise in demand in recent years. There
OL,10,Fare currently around 2,500 patients
OL,11,Fwaiting to access the service. We
OL,12,Fclinically assess patients and
OL,13,Fprioritise them according to the
OL,14,Fseverity of their condition and
OL,15,Ftherefore waiting times vary."
OL,17,FWhen asked why she wanted to speak out
OL,18,Fso candidly, Michelle said: "I just
OL,19,Fwant to get this solved. At the moment
OL,20,FI keep thinking what's wrong with me,
OL,21,Fwhy can't I be normal?
