OL,3,C'Sleep disorder has taken over my
OL,4,Clife': Charity warns of a sleep
OL,5,Cpandemic
OL,7,F"Nobody seems to suffer like I do. But
OL,8,Fperhaps people do but they just don't
OL,9,Ftalk about it".
OL,11,FLisa Artis, deputy CEO of The Sleep
OL,12,FCharity, an organisation dedicated to
OL,13,Fsupporting sleep in the UK, told ITV
OL,14,FWales the current sleep landscape is
OL,15,Fas bad as it has ever been.
OL,17,FRecent research conducted by the
OL,18,Fcharity has shown around 9 in 10
OL,19,Fpeople across the UK are experiencing
OL,20,Fproblems with their sleep.
